<phoenix_dataset_evaluators_context>
  <description>The dataset evaluators tab is currently mounted. This is the only surface where `create_code_evaluator` is advertised, because committing a new code evaluator requires the slideover that this page can mount. The user can review, accept, and save evaluator proposals here.</description>
  <dataset_node_id format="phoenix_node_id">{{ dataset_evaluators.dataset_node_id }}</dataset_node_id>
{% if dataset_evaluators.dataset_version_node_id %}
  <dataset_version_node_id format="phoenix_node_id">{{ dataset_evaluators.dataset_version_node_id }}</dataset_version_node_id>
{% endif %}
  <three_stage_flow>
    The `create_code_evaluator` tool drives a three-stage flow:
    1. Explain in chat what evaluator you intend to author and why it fits the user's request.
    2. Call `create_code_evaluator` exactly once with the full proposal — this renders an inline diff preview in the chat. Do NOT call any GraphQL mutation directly; the tool call does not persist anything.
    3. The user clicks Confirm on the preview to open a prefilled slideover, where they review and Save. The Save is what persists the evaluator and binds it to this dataset. If the user clicks Reject (in chat) or Cancel (in the slideover), nothing is persisted.
  </three_stage_flow>
{% if not has_usable_sandbox %}
  <sandbox_unavailable>
    No usable sandbox configuration is currently enabled for this Phoenix instance, so creating a code evaluator on this dataset is not possible right now. If the user asks to create one, direct them to visit `/settings/sandboxes` to enable a sandbox provider first.
  </sandbox_unavailable>
{% endif %}
</phoenix_dataset_evaluators_context>
